The game Totolospi (War) is played by two players on a noshape board with nobasis tiling. All players play with Counters. Rules for Pieces: Counters hop adjacent or step adjacent. Players take turns moving. Setup: Place a Counter for player one at the intersection of the bottom sites of the board and the left sites of the board expanded by 9 steps. Place a Counter for player two at the intersection of the top sites of the board and the right sites of the board expanded by 9 steps.. Rules: Move one of your pieces. Aim: If the next player cannot move, the next player loses. The Totolospi (War) (Ludii 1) ruleset.
